OL,3,CMet Office confirms Thursday is the
OL,4,Chottest start to May on record
OL,6,FKew Gardens, in south-west London,
OL,7,Fregistered 29.3C on Thursday
OL,8,Fafternoon, the Met Office said, taking
OL,9,Fit past the previous May 1 record high
OL,10,Ftemperature of 27.4C at Lossiemouth in
OL,11,FMoray in 1990.
OL,13,FThis is now the warmest May 1 since
OL,14,F1860.
OL,16,FThursday was also the warmest day of
OL,17,Fthe year so far beating the previous
OL,18,Fhigh of 26.7C reached in Wisley,
OL,19,FSurrey, on Wednesday, the agency said.
